# **BrainDrive Visual Brand Guidelines**

Consistent brand presentation isn't just about recognition—it's about rallying people to choose personal AI ownership over corporate control. Use this guide to ensure BrainDrive's visual identity remains clear, bold, and true to our mission to make it easy for everyone to build, control, and benefit from their own AI system.

## **1\. Brand Identity**

BrainDrive represents **freedom, ownership, empowerment, and** **sustainability** in the AI space. Our visual identity balances a **professional, minimalist design** with **strategic vibrant elements** to create a brand that feels both **trustworthy and innovative**.

### **File Formats for Logo Usage**

Light and Dark mode logo files are linked in the format column below. 

| Format | Usage |
| ----- | ----- |
| [**SVG**](https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1HJhuUZPyXNUVlA_DR33VvHbS6UZgbWY_?usp=sharing) **(.svg)** | Best for web, digital applications, and UI; infinitely scalable. |
| [**PNG**](https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1of9ZbRnFaoCNLzFygdI7xGiTi4nmjZJz?usp=drive_link) **(.png)** | Digital use with transparency support; best for websites and social media. |
| [**JPG**](https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1YkJlzHRbSGwcP3as1goj7la2s1g8Vv5-?usp=drive_link) **(.jpg)** | Suitable for web and social media but does not support transparency. |

### **Clear Space & Minimum Size**

* Maintain a clear space around the logo equal to at least **x-height** of the "B" in BrainDrive.  
* The logo should never be displayed smaller than **100px in width** to ensure readability.

### **Incorrect Usage**

* **Avoid** stretching, distorting, or recoloring the logo.  
* **Avoid** adding drop shadows or additional effects.  
* **Avoid** placing on cluttered backgrounds that reduce legibility.

## **4\. Typography**

### **Primary Font (Logo & Headings): Montserrat**

* **Usage:** Logo, main headers, call-to-actions  
* **Weights:** Bold (700-900)  
* **Why?** Clean, geometric sans-serif that conveys professionalism and innovation  
* **Italic:** Used for emphasis in supporting text or quotes.  
* **Uppercase:** Reserved for short, impactful headers or navigation labels.

  ### **Secondary Font (Subheadings & Body Text): Questrial**

* **Usage:** Subheadings, UI elements, body text  
* **Weights:** Regular (400-500)  
* **Why?** Modern, rounded sans-serif with excellent readability for digital content  
* **Italic:** Used for emphasis in supporting text or quotes.  
* **Uppercase:** Reserved for short, impactful headers or navigation labels.

### **Typography Implementation**

| Element | Font | Weight |
| :---- | :---- | :---- |
| Logo & Main Headers | Montserrat | Bold (700-900) |
| Subheadings & UI Elements | Questrial | Medium (500-600) |
| Body Text (Docs, Website) | Questrial | Regular (400-500) |
| Call-to-Actions | Questrialt | Regular (400-500) |

## **5\. Call-to-Action Buttons**

### **Light Mode Buttons**

* **Primary CTA Buttons:** CTA Black (\#000000) with White text (\#FFFFFF)  
* **Secondary Buttons:** Midnight Blue (\#0A152A) with White text  
* **Tertiary Buttons:** Steel Blue (\#325D87) with White text

### **Dark Mode Buttons**

* **Primary CTA Buttons:** CTA White (\#FFFFFF) with Deep Blue text (\#03050A)  
* **Secondary Buttons:** Steel Blue (\#325D87) with White text  
* **Tertiary Buttons:** Gray Blue (\#1E2A3B) with Sky Blue text

## **6\. UI Elements**

### **Light Mode UI**

| Element | Color |
| ----- | ----- |
| Card Backgrounds | White (\#FFFFFF) |
| Page Backgrounds | Soft White (\#FAFAFA) |
| Dividers/Borders | Light Blue (\#C5DAED) |
| Standard Icons | Deep Blue (\#03050A) or Midnight Blue (\#0A152A) |
| Primary Accent Elements | Steel Blue (\#325D87) |
| Selection States | Steel Blue at 15-20% opacity |
| Success States | Green (\#28A745) |
| Warning States | Orange (\#FFA500) |
| Error States | Red (\#DC3545) |

### **Dark Mode UI**

| Element | Color |
| ----- | ----- |
| Card Backgrounds | Gray Blue (\#1E2A3B) |
| Page Backgrounds | Background Dark (\#03050A) |
| Dividers/Borders | Secondary Dark (\#0A152A) |
| Standard Icons | Light Blue (\#C5DAED) or Sky Blue (\#7CA7D1) |
| Primary Accent Elements | Steel Blue (\#325D87) |
| Selection States | Steel Blue at 20-25% opacity |
| Success States | Green (\#2DCE89) |
| Warning States | Orange (\#FFA500) |
| Error States | Red (\#F5365C) |

## **7\. Mode Switching & Accessibility**

* Implement a prominent, accessible toggle between **light and dark modes**  
* Save user preference for future visits  
* Default to system preference but allow manual override  
* **Minimum Contrast Ratio:**  
  * Text: **4.5:1** in both modes  
  * Icons/Interactive Elements: **3:1**  
* **Focus States:** Visible indicators for all interactive elements  
* **Avoid using color alone** to convey meaning; pair with text/icons

## **8\. Example Applications**

### **Homepage Header**

* **Light Mode:** Deep Blue text on Soft White background, CTA Black for buttons  
* **Dark Mode:** Light Blue text on Background Dark, CTA White for buttons

### **Documentation**

* **Light Mode:** Deep Blue headings, Dark Gray body text, Soft White background  
* **Dark Mode:** Light Blue headings, Light Gray body text, Background Dark

### **Interactive Platform**

* **Light Mode:** White cards on Soft White background, CTA Black primary buttons  
* **Dark Mode:** Gray Blue cards on Background Dark, CTA White primary buttons

## **9\. Final Notes**

By following these standards, we create a recognizable brand that builds trust and advances our vision of a world where individuals—not Big Tech—own their AI future.

Whether you're designing for digital platforms, marketing materials, or product interfaces, these guidelines will help you create visuals that align with our revolutionary approach to AI ownership. Remember: every visual element should reinforce that with BrainDrive, it's your AI, your rules.
